          "targets": [
          "sm_100a",
          "ptx93"
          ],
          "representation": "nvJitLink cubins retaining the combined 24-route tcgen05 kernel",
          "stage": "device_link",
          "mechanism": "inline_ptx",
          "outcome": "succeeded",
          "artifact_kind": "cubin",
          "detail": "CUDA 13.3 nvJitLink accepted every route on sm_100a, sm_103a, and sm_110a. Cubin SHA-256 was 1bab3647f9af53b36a52caa8323aeeacdf4244386f1ab0584e9823dcc1f13014, 57f3f660825a5d2970b34127c72cee000291ae352e4a33b508998bb0410d8a75, and 9bb5d9ded614b742960d19ed430d0f91a0fb8c90e675c7912c664cbad695a2de. The same exact LTO route reached PTX but cubin linking rejected every family on sm_120a and sm_121a; those architectures are deliberately excluded.",
